## Testing expectations

The final implementation must include **focused tests** proving:

* Valid `support.reply_draft` and `support.escalate` drafts map to Django-compatible action payloads
* Unsupported action types are rejected by the mapper
* Step 9.1 approval metadata (`requires_approval`, `matched_policy_code`, `risk_level`, `safety_notes`) is preserved in mapped payloads
* `dry_run=True` returns mapped payloads without POSTing to Django
* Explicit persistence POSTs to `POST /internal/ai/actions/` via mocked `DjangoClient`
* Persistence failure surfaces safe warnings without discarding validated `SupportInsights`
* Mapped payloads contain safe fields only â€” no raw PII in tests or examples
* Optional `/run` persistence wiring (if added) follows Sales/Content Agent patterns

Use synthetic, sanitized fixtures only. Do not include real customer data in tests.

