## Acceptance criteria

* Validated `SupportReplyDraft` items map to Django-compatible action payloads
* Only `support.reply_draft` and `support.escalate` are supported
* Mapped payloads use safe fields only; Step 9.1 approval metadata is preserved
* Step 9.2 refusal, Step 9.3 prompt-injection, Step 9.4 schema validation, Step 9.5 sanitized context, and Step 9.6 runtime pipeline behavior are preserved
* `dry_run` mode produces mapped payloads without POSTing to Django
* Persistence uses shared `DjangoClient` and `POST /internal/ai/actions/` only when explicitly requested
* Persistence failure adds safe warnings and does not discard validated `SupportInsights`
* Focused deterministic tests cover mapping, dry-run, persistence, and failure paths without real LLM API keys or external services
* No customer contact, Instagram DMs, refunds, order mutation, payments, pricing/inventory changes, publishing, real external side effects, direct DB access, or Prestia-specific hardcoding
* No full message bodies or raw payload bodies logged at INFO level; no raw PII in fixtures/logs
* Step 9.8 acceptance proof and `docs/examples/support_output.json` are not implemented in this step
* `docs/phases/step-9.7.md` documents the implementation
